OL,7,F"The systems we've got are not
OL,8,Fdesigned to deal with complexity," he
OL,9,Fexplained. "They're not designed to
OL,10,Frespond compassionately over a very,
OL,11,Fvery long period of time.
OL,13,F"It's about moving people along as
OL,14,Fquickly as possible. So the complexity
OL,15,Fof people's trauma isn't dealt with
OL,16,Fand that is the reason why we're
OL,17,Freally seeing rises in the people
OL,18,Fdying."
